<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry reports that he has commenced arrangement to secure peace
                            between the Government of Salvador and Guatemalan Government. Says he
                            will advise by cable progress of the negotiations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>